---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/tools';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Contact Workspace Lux"
  description="Get in touch with Workspace Lux for questions, feedback, corrections, or partnership inquiries about our lighting calculators and guides."
  path="/contact"
>
  <article class="max-w-site mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-10 prose-content">
    <header class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-main mb-4">Contact</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-muted max-w-3xl">
        We welcome questions about our calculators, content corrections, and collaboration ideas.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>Email</h2>
    <p>
      The fastest way to reach us is by email:
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="text-primary hover:underline">{SITE.email}</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      We read every message. Response times vary, but we aim to reply within a few business days.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact form</h2>
    <p>
      A contact form powered by Formspree will be added here. Replace the placeholder below with your
      Formspree endpoint when ready:
    </p>
    <div class="card p-6 my-6 border-dashed">
      <p class="text-sm text-muted mb-4">
        Formspree placeholder — set <code class="text-main">action="https://formspree.io/f/YOUR_FORM_ID"</code>
        on the form when your endpoint is configured.
      </p>
      <form action="https://formspree.io/f/placeholder" method="POST" class="space-y-4 max-w-lg">
        <div>
          <label for="name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-main mb-1.5">Name</label>
          <input
            id="name"
            name="name"
            type="text"
            required
            class="input-field"
            autocomplete="name"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-medium text-main mb-1.5">Email</label>
          <input
            id="email"
            name="email"
            type="email"
            required
            class="input-field"
            autocomplete="email"
          />
        </div>
        <div>
          <label for="message" class="block text-sm font-medium text-main mb-1.5">Message</label>
          <textarea
            id="message"
            name="message"
            rows="5"
            required
            class="input-field h-auto py-3"
          />
        </div>
        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Send message</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <h2>What to include</h2>
    <p>
      For calculator issues, please share the page URL, inputs you used, and what you expected vs what
      you saw. For content feedback, point to the specific section. We appreciate clear reports — they
      help us improve the site for everyone.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
